<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Rampage</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Mob will hit the top 2-5 people (varies by mob) on their hate list, regardless of where they are (also varies by mob). It's almost like an AoE melee attack on those that have irritated the mob most. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Enrage</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Mob will autoriposte all attacks in its front arc. Which means, basically, if you're in front and still attacking when you see the message you'll skewer yourself. To avoid that stay behind the mob (except the MT of course) if you are on the sides or not sure if the mob is turning towards you, turn off autoattack when you see &quot;Mob_X has become Enraged&quot;. Mobs that enrage do so when they hit about 10% health and will remain that way for about 12 seconds.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Flurry</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Mob gets extra attacks on its target. Usually 2 or 3 extra hits on top of the 2/3/4 it already does per round. All the hits land, it's lots of fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The Shaman/Enchanter spell Cripple can lessen the frequency of flurries and rampaging for the most part. It really depends on the mob. <p>~*<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=344457>Kirae</a>*~
